The '''British Energy Efficiency Federation''' (or '''BEEF''') was founded in 1996 by the [[Her Majesty's Government|United Kingdom Government]] to provide a forum for consultation between existing industry associations in the energy sector.<ref name="BEEF1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ukace.org/pubs/consult/beefTreasResp.pdf |accessdate=2007-06-26 |date=2002-10-07 |title=Economic Instruments to improve household energy |work=Letter to HM Treasury |author=BEEF (Andrew Warren, chair) |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071006140613/http://www.ukace.org/pubs/consult/beefTreasResp.pdf |archivedate=2007-10-06 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
