'''Einar Westye Egeberg Jr.''' (24 February 1883 – 1946) was a Norwegian businessperson.
He was born in [[Oslo|Kristiania]]. After middle school he attended the [[Öffentlichen Handelslehranstalt]] in [[Leipzig]] from 1899 to 1902. He worked with timber trade in [[London]] from 1902 to 1904 and studied languages in [[France]] from 1906 to 1907. In 1911 he became a manager and co-owner in the family company [[Westye Egeberg & Co]].<ref name=merkbio>{{cite encyclopedia|year=1935|title=Egeberg, Einar Westye jr.|encyclopedia=[[Merkantilt biografisk leksikon]]|editor-last=Hoffstad|editor-first=Einar|editor-link=Einar Hoffstad|publisher=Yrkesforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://runeberg.org/merkbio/0256.html|page=178|language=Norwegian|accessdate=25 February 2011}}</ref> The company was founded by [[Westye Egeberg]] (1770–1830) in 1802, and had been passed down through the generations.<ref name=snl2>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Egeberg|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Egeberg|language=Norwegian|accessdate=25 February 2011}}</ref> Egeberg also took over the estates Stormo and Tannæs in [[Nord-Odal]] in 1930. His interests were skiing and hunting.<ref name=merkbio/> He was a member of the gentlemen's club [[SK Fram (Oslo)|SK Fram]] from 1912 to 1942.<ref>{{cite book|editor=Qvale, Fredrik|editor-link=Fredrik Qvale|year=1989|title=Skiklubben Fram 100 år|language=Norwegian|pages=9–11}}</ref>
He died in 1946, and was buried at [[Vestre gravlund]]. His daughter Agnes Cecilie Egeberg, whom he had together with Kitty Parr (1892–1970), married cruise line director [[Hans Christian Henriksen]].<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=1973|title=Henriksen, Hans Chr|encyclopedia=[[Hvem er hvem?]]|editor=Steenstrup, Bjørn|publisher=Aschehoug|location=Oslo|url=http://runeberg.org/hvemerhvem/1973/0235.html|page=235|language=Norwegian|accessdate=25 February 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disnorge.no/gravminner/vis.php?mode=x|title=Cemeteries in Norway|publisher=DIS-Norge|language=Norwegian|accessdate=25 February 2011}}</ref>
