{{Infobox person | name = Filippo Ghirelli | image = | alt = Filippo Ghirelli | caption = Filippo Ghirelli | birth_name = Filippo Ghirelli | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1980|01|23}} | birth_place = [[Rome]], [[Italy]] | nationality = Italian | father = Francesco Ghirelli | mother = Maria Carla Pelosi Ghirelli | spouse = Daniela Di Giorgio | children = Sofia and Francesco | known_for = [[Investments]], [[philanthropy]], [[Sustainable energy]] }}
'''Filippo Ghirelli''' (born 23 January 1980) is an [[Italy|Italian]] entrepreneur and philanthropist. Filippo is founder and CEO of Genera Group Holdings<ref>{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/officers/70wDMNDUXU-wzRDF1IAzr6LN0iQ/appointments|title=Filippo GHIRELLI - Personal Appointments (free information from Companies House)|publisher=}}</ref> which operates in energy production and efficiency, real estate development, general construction contract and diversified investments.
==Biography== Filippo was born in an Italian family of real estate entrepreneurs in [[Rome]], attended international schools and graduated from University of Rome in Civil Engineering with further specialization courses in [[MIT]]. Also he got a Master in [[Business Administration]] and a Master in Financial Markets degrees.
After BA degree he started his career as Project Engineer in [[Guinea]], [[Ghana]] and [[Mali]] working with various construction multinationals. Later on he returned to Italy to follow high speed train infrastructures. In 2007 he became General Manager for De Angelis Group. After sudden death of founder, Filippo started his own construction business with Italian and international projects in 2009. Also, he has been the director and shareholder of Leaf Investments,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.checkdirector.co.uk/director/filippo-ghirelli/|title=Filippo Ghirelli, director at Genera Capital Ltd, London|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leafinvestments.net/|title=Leaf Investments - early stage investor in learning technology businesses|publisher=}}</ref> an investment boutique based in London. Later he opened a retail real estate development company and started to invest in energy assets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.renovapower.com/it/grandi-impianti|title=Renova Power|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.luiss.edu/news/2016/01/29/becoming-professional-sustainable-economy|title=Becoming a professional in the sustainable economy|publisher=}}</ref> Ghirelli’s group presently operates in various countries, such as Italy, Morocco, Algeria, Spain and the UAE and has JV’s with major multinationals and banks like [[Unicredit Group]]. He refers to Italian intellectuals and also he is board member of JP Morgan inspired Canova Club.
Filippo has been actively involved in Italian business community life, visited events such as "The people of the bills and the disappearance of the most protected market",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stopsecret.it/Eventi/06-DICEMBRE-2016---ROMA---Convegno-Il-popolo-delle-bollette147621891852232/Il-programma-dellauevento-Il-popolo-delle-bollette-e-la-sco147630174617655|title=Il programma dell’evento|publisher=}}</ref> “The companies and banks in the state of crisis of competence, responsibility and prevention”.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diciommoandpartners.com/2016/04/29/le-imprese-e-le-banche-nello-stato-di-crisi-convegno-a-saint-vincent-il-30-04-2015/|title="Le imprese e le banche nello stato di crisi" - Convegno a Saint Vincent il 30.04.2016 -|date=29 April 2016|publisher=}}</ref>
Filippo’s philanthropic activities include active participation and support to young artists’ careers and sponsorship events like the Everland show,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.evershow.it/lo-show-everland-per-emergenza-sorrisi-ieri-al-salone-margherita/|title=Lo show Everland per Emergenza Sorrisi ieri al Salone Margherita|publisher=}}</ref> supporter of [[Save the Children]], Emergenza Sorrisi and Peter Pan Onlus.
==Assets== Filippo owns Genera Group Holdings which also invests in R&D and acts as incubator for start-ups. Through his company, Ghirelli holds shares in lots of other companies. He pursues the idea of clear “green” energy and investing in innovative and sustainable projects such as “Copernico” and “Healthadvisor” which are providing useful service for society. His group has recently seen the entrance of german investment fund IKAV Invest with available resources exceeding 350 M€. Filippo was also involved [[RCD Mallorca|football team Mallorca]] acquisition in late 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ultimahora.es/deportes/real-mallorca/2014/11/06/137309/ghirelli-expone-tratado-inteciones-para-real-mallorca.html|title=Ghirelli expone su tratado de intenciones para el Real Mallorca|date=6 November 2014|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/2014/11/07/futbol/equipos/mallorca/1415367918.html|title=Filippo Ghirelli está dispuesto a comprar el Mallorca|first=|last=MARCA.com|date=7 November 2014|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elmundo.es/baleares/2014/09/24/54228e4122601d6c478b4570.html|title=La hora de Filippo Ghirelli|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diariodemallorca.es/rcd-mallorca/2014/11/20/ghirelli-busca-acuerdo-compra-serra/977975.html|title=Ghirelli busca un acuerdo de compra con Serra y Cerdà|first=Diario de|last=Mallorca|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.estadiodeportivo.com/betis/2014/12/17/ghirelli-revela-venta-express-fallida-serra/34637.html|title=Ghirelli revela una venta express fallida con Serra|first=Estadio|last=deportivo|publisher=}}</ref>
